  <h1> Major Cities in Scotland </h1>
  <p> Edinburgh: About 500,000 people live in Edinburgh, but don't let the small population distract you from the city's fascinating history and culture.
  The best way to explore Edinburgh is on foot because of the small size of the city. Attractions here include
the Edinburgh Zoo, which is one of the most renowned zoo's in the world. Edinburgh also has the world famous icon of
Scotland, the legendary Edinburgh Castle which houses the Crown Jewels, One
O’Clock Gun, Half Moon Battery, and the national war museum and memorial. There
are many historical monuments including the Scott Monument, Nelson Monument, and the
National Monument of Scotland. If you are interested in Medieval Culture and more of the history related part of Scotland you can visit the various castles including 
the Lauriston Castle, Craigmillar Castle, and obviously the Edinburgh Castle. To read more about the attractions, please reference the Tourism tab. </p>
